item.title: Chat in Verse
item.dc:creator: OldDirtyBastard
item.description:
Comrade Tiki:

Mirth is simply what I feel about your worth.
To think you’ve only come this far from your birth
is an agonizing thought to historians and me
who would rather think a human being can have destiny
beyond that of spewing fat on everybody’s bacon,
raking in feedback which makes his mother hate him.

Your know, she cries… every night she spends at my house
'cause I have your eyes, and remind her of you, during the things we do.
But now we’ve gone wise with a position new.
She appreciates my size, and stays turned away from me, until we’re both blue.

Your father’s not dead,
I’m your father, dude,
and, son, I’m disappoint.

I think I’ve made my point.

ahem
RJ Berger lost his grip
I am satisfied
